- id: validate-mime
  subject: Validate detectMime magic-byte detection for all 35 formats
  status: pending
  description: |
    Witness detectMime returning correct MIME for representative magic bytes
    of each detected format. Cover: PNG, JPEG, GIF, WebP, PDF, ZIP, GZIP,
    MP4, WebM, MP3, WAV, FLAC, OGG, Arrow, Parquet, MsgPack magic bytes.
  effort: small
  category: infra
  blocking: []
  blockedBy: []
  acceptance:
    - PNG magic bytes return image/png
    - JPEG magic bytes return image/jpeg
    - PDF magic bytes return application/pdf
    - ZIP magic bytes return application/zip
    - unknown bytes return application/octet-stream
    - at least 10 formats verified with real magic bytes
  edge_cases:
    - empty Uint8Array does not throw
    - 1-byte input does not throw

- id: validate-framing
  subject: Validate stdio framing encode/decode round-trips for all three framing types
  status: pending
  description: |
    Witness: length-prefix framing (binary chunk), ndjson framing (json chunk),
    newline framing (text chunk) — encode then decode back through the same
    stdinChunks/writeToStdout pipeline logic. Verify boundary correctness for
    multi-chunk sequences.
  effort: small
  category: infra
  blocking: []
  blockedBy: []
  acceptance:
    - length-prefix: binary chunk survives encode/decode with correct bytes
    - ndjson: json chunk survives encode/decode with correct data
    - newline: text chunk survives encode/decode with correct string
    - multi-chunk sequence decoded in order without corruption
  edge_cases:
    - empty binary payload (null chunk) framed and decoded correctly
    - json with unicode survives ndjson round-trip

- id: validate-operator-composition
  subject: Validate operators chained into real processor pipelines end-to-end
  status: pending
  description: |
    Witness operators composed with createProcessor and pipe():
    source -> gate -> scan -> batch pipeline producing correct output.
    mux two sources through take(5) pipeline.
    split stream into two branches with different transforms.
  effort: small
  category: infra
  blocking: []
  blockedBy: []
  acceptance:
    - gate->scan->batch pipeline produces correct batched running totals
    - mux->take produces exactly N items from merged sources
    - split branches receive identical input and transform independently
  edge_cases:
    - empty source through operator chain emits nothing
    - single-item source through batch(10) emits one batch of 1

- id: validate-error-paths
  subject: Validate error propagation through processor and codec
  status: pending
  description: |
    Witness: codec decode failure throws with context, processor catching
    transform error sets status=error, malformed ndjson input throws.
  effort: small
  category: infra
  blocking: []
  blockedBy: []
  acceptance:
    - decodeChunk with invalid bytes throws Error with message context
    - createProcessor with throwing transform sets state.status to error
    - error is surfaced (not swallowed) when start() is awaited
  edge_cases:
    - error in mid-stream (after some chunks processed) still sets error state
